- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper discusses machine translation systems and their training on textual resources. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also likely as the paper focuses on translating spoken language data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of neural models for machine translation. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the paper discusses the robustness of sentence encoding approaches for NMT encoder-decoder modeling. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the evaluation of NMT systems on textual inputs.
